      "q1": "What is this?",
      "a1": "Artists build Rubik's-cube mosaics from hundreds or thousands of cubes. The hardest part is converting a photo into a 6-color pixelated version. This tool does that for you and produces a printable PDF assembly guide.",
      "q2": "Does it work with black stickers?",
      "a2": "Yes. Open the Palette editor and enable black. You can add, remove, or recolor the palette however you like.",
      "q3": "Can I upload a pre-made miniature?",
      "a3": "Yes. If you already have a pixel-perfect miniature (e.g. 60x90 px for a 20x30 cube mosaic), rename it to start with 'miniature' and drop it in — the tool will skip straight to the export stage.",
      "q4": "Why do some images work better than others?",
      "a4": "High-contrast, well-lit source photos work best. Beauty filters that smooth facial features tend to destroy the information the dithering step needs. Grayscale photos are fine."
